    <briefdescription>
<para>Callable wrapper around a compiled parser expression with <computeroutput>N</computeroutput> variables. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Instances are returned by <ref refid="classamrex_1_1Parser_1a84c2f77f7586faf9e89ef87489297bfa" kindref="member">Parser::compile()</ref> / <ref refid="classamrex_1_1Parser_1a2bcb71246d0395f1f9c3ce37e2286c09" kindref="member">Parser::compileHost()</ref> and may be invoked on host or device. Device execution is available only when AMREX_USE_GPU is enabled and a device executor buffer has been created.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>N</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of variables referenced in the expression. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
